CATHERINE TAYLOR v. HUGH CULBREATH, as Sheriff etc. 19 So. (2nd) 510

June Term, 1944

October 31, 1944 Division A *68Bryan & Bryan, for appellant. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and John C. Wynn, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

Upon consideration of the motion to dismiss the appeal in this cause it appearing that the charge against appellant has been dismissed and. that she has been discharged from custody, it is ordered that the cause be remanded to the circuit court with directions to enter an order discharging petitioner under the writ of habeas corpus.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, CHAPMAN and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
